  "text": "In ARDS and ALI patients, risk factors for mortality and/ or prolonged mechanical ventilation have been identified, which include the following: initial pH, [CITATION_1] [CITATION_2] initial inspiratory pressure and oxygenation index. [CITATION_3] [CITATION_4] In our population, we also identified inspiratory pressure, pH, PaO 2 / FiO 2 , oxygenation index at T0 but only oxygenation index at T1 of MV. No difference PEEP and tidal volume between survivors and non-survivors was observed. It is possible that such difference exists but the present study had insufficient statistical power to detect it.",
